00:29:06.380 --> 00:29:07.170
That one.

00:29:07.170 --> 00:29:08.090
I like.

00:29:08.090 --> 00:29:10.700
That one I don't like.

00:29:10.700 --> 00:29:13.384
That one is unstable.

00:29:13.384 --> 00:29:15.800
So the question is, how can
you make a magnetic levitation

00:29:15.800 --> 00:29:16.299
system?

00:29:16.299 --> 00:29:18.200
How do you make a
system that we use

00:29:18.200 --> 00:29:23.250
a magnet to levitate a mass when
the physics are intrinsically

00:29:23.250 --> 00:29:23.910
stable?

00:29:23.910 --> 00:29:26.980
And the answer is--

00:29:26.980 --> 00:29:29.170
feedback, of course, yes.

00:29:29.170 --> 00:29:31.900
So the idea is that
here is our system that

00:29:31.900 --> 00:29:34.090
was intrinsically unstable.

00:29:34.090 --> 00:29:37.992
What we'd like to do is
somehow change the physics.

00:29:37.992 --> 00:29:39.700
One of the ways we
can change the physics

00:29:39.700 --> 00:29:43.656
is by modifying the current
that runs through the magnet.

00:29:43.656 --> 00:29:45.280
If we changed the
current from i naught

00:29:45.280 --> 00:29:47.225
to 1.1 times i naught,
then the forces

00:29:47.225 --> 00:29:48.350
everywhere would be bigger.

00:29:50.970 --> 00:29:54.690
We could use that idea to
introduce a second feedback

00:29:54.690 --> 00:29:55.540
path.

00:29:55.540 --> 00:29:57.480
There is the intrinsic
one that comes just

00:29:57.480 --> 00:29:58.950
from the physical layout.

00:29:58.950 --> 00:30:03.720
But I'm going to add a path that
senses the position of the mass

00:30:03.720 --> 00:30:06.100
and feeds back a
change in current.

00:30:06.100 --> 00:30:10.350
And if I do this carefully,
I can arrange this path,

00:30:10.350 --> 00:30:14.310
the intrinsic one has positive
feedback that was bad,

00:30:14.310 --> 00:30:19.600
but the one I add has negative
feedback, which is good.

00:30:19.600 --> 00:30:23.920
Then the overall system looks
more like this where I've got

00:30:23.920 --> 00:30:27.930
